### Problem Statement

Centralized systems perpetuate power imbalances, data breaches, financial exploitation, and governance opacity. In developed nations, incidents like Equifax hacks (147M users affected) highlight data risks. In developing countries in africa, Asia, latin America etc, mobile money systems (e.g., MTN, Airtel in uganda) impose high fees, outages, arbitrary account freezes during unrest, and corruption. Globally, users lack ownership of identity, data, assets, and interactions, leading to dependency, manipulation, and single-point failures. CIVITAS solves this by providing a parallel, voluntary decentralized ecosystem that restores sovereignty without replacing governments.

